EXISTS and NOT EXISTS in SQL
1) Definition :
    EXISTS: Checks if a subquery returns any rows. Returns TRUE if at least one row exists.

     NOT EXISTS: Checks if a subquery returns no rows. Returns TRUE if no rows exist.

* Syntax :
-- EXISTS  
SELECT columns  
FROM table1  
WHERE EXISTS (subquery);  

-- NOT EXISTS  
SELECT columns  
FROM table1  
WHERE NOT EXISTS (subquery);  
